 needed. If there aren’t extra dependencies, Docker, or environment requirements, I think it makes sense to stick with \\\"no_action.\\\" However, including some form of agent guidance could be useful, like advising users to set environment variables or system properties. If test-code setup is necessary, such as with Spring context and @EnableCommand, perhaps \\\"advisory_preparation\\\" could apply. But I need to ensure I don't recommend modifying the repository.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No concrete extra setup is required: spring-shell-core 4.0.2 resolves its required Spring Framework, Hibernate Validator, Jakarta Validation, and Jakarta EL dependencies transitively, and the official core hello-world sample uses only spring-shell-core plus normal Spring context bootstrapping.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Spring Shell has optional Spring Boot test utilities such as spring-shell-test-autoconfigure, but they are not required to exercise the core artifact and would broaden the test scope.\",\n    \"Tests should avoid requiring a real interactive terminal; core APIs can be exercised through command registration, parsing, and non-interactive command execution.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0488a02cc206b316016a3f0cb3782c8195b5ad9d55326ca780\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2259, "output": 869, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30264, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782516903232, "responseId": "resp_0488a02cc206b316016a3f0ca7c9bc81959b8582709ce83f77"}, "toolResults": []}
